I bought all of these games when they first came out. They were full games to buy. After a few years I decided to play again, because games usually came with a restore purchases. Well, come to find out they have now joined the ranks of making people pay monthly even if they bought the full games before. After pressing restore purchases, they are still completely full of ads every second, I guess unless I pay monthly for what I had already paid for in full. I miss pay once and then play that games use to have.

The game play itself is really fun, but there are too many ads and it’s $10 a month to turn off ads! Most games marketed towards a younger audience only ask for a one time fee of $2 to turn off ads and I’d be more than happy to pay that but $10 a month to not see ads every time my daughter completes a level is too much! The game has changed so much to the point that game play is too easy and just not engaging for my 6 year old

title.label: Perfect example of mobile game greed

content.label: Wow this game took a nosedive since I last downloaded it. Decided to revisit it today because I’ve always enjoyed this game and it hits a weird nostalgia point for me, and wow have they ruined it! The ads are so frequent and invasive they make the game unplayable, more than half of your time spent on the app will be closing ads as opposed to actually playing the game. And to add insult to injury, no longer is it a .99 or even a $1.99 to get rid of the ads, no no no my friend. It’s part of a bundle that’s $9.99 + fees a month! They expect me to pay the same amount as a Netflix/Spotify subscription for a mobile game app with nowhere even close to the content and value of ANY subscription service or real any other $10 purchase you could make ANYWHERE else on practically ANYTHING else. This is insulting, and if you pay this ridiculous subscription cost you should be publicly stoned and your money should be taken from you and used to feed starving children because you aren’t capable of managing it properly but the sad thing is they’re most likely only staying afloat through young kids stealing mommy and daddy’s credit card without their knowledge because nobody in their right mind would spend that much money on this game. The developers/creators/owners of this app are downright despicable, slimy, gross, greedy people and do not deserve your money. I will be uninstalling and will not give any business to this company or any companies with practices like this. I suggest you do the same. Stop taking advantage of gamers and children. You’re scammers is what you are. DO NOT DOWNLOAD.
